quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “O you disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,I will never worship what you worship
  109,5,nor will you ever worship what I worship
  109,6,"You have your way, and I have my Way.”"
  110,1,When God’s ˹ultimate˺ help comes and the victory ˹over Mecca is achieved˺
  110,2,and you ˹O Prophet˺ see the people embracing God’s Way in crowds
  110,3,"then glorify the praises of your Lord and seek His forgiveness, for certainly He is ever Accepting of Repentance"
  111,1,"May the hands of Abu Lahab perish, and he ˹himself˺ perish"
  111,2,Neither his wealth nor ˹worldly˺ gains will benefit him
  111,3,He will burn in a flaming Fire
  111,4,"and ˹so will˺ his wife, the carrier of ˹thorny˺ kindling"
  111,5,around her neck will be a rope of palm-fibre